			<div class="content" id="post-content-1918128">
									

<p>SCP-006 &quot;Eric's toy&quot;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-066 rolled away again and produced the phrase “Are you Eric?”</p>
</blockquote>
<p>SCP-168</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Upon initial inspection, it was discovered that the name “Eric” was carved into the inside of the removable casing.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Okay, I assumed this was a coincidence. Now I'm not so sure. What are the odds of three SCP items that bear or generate the name of the same kid? Shouldn't the Foundation try to figure out who this person was to ascertain a possible connection?</p>

